1a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Alli AI is best suited for agencies, multi site management, technical SEO, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Serpstat, meanwhile, shines for SMBs, in house SEOs, budget teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Alli AI describes itself as \"AI-powered on-page SEO automation that implements changes at scale.\" Serpstat, established in 2013, positions itself as \"Growth hacking SEO tool for keyword research, rank tracking, and site audit.\" With 6 years between them, Serpstat brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Alli AI offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
1b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Serpstat** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 3), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Alli AI is a poor choice — far from it. Alli AI excels in its own right, particularly for agencies and multi site management.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value good value for comprehensive features, go with Serpstat. If automatically implements seo changes matters more to you, Alli AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
